methods.fillChunkAppend:
Appends the values referenced by orderKeys onto destination.  orderKeys are assumed
 to be entirely contained on this Page.

:param context: io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.ChunkSource.FillContext
:param destination: io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.WritableChunk<? superio.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.Attributes.DictionaryKeys>
:param orderedKeys: io.deephaven.db.v2.utils.OrderedKeys
methods.getLong:
Get a single long from this region.

*Overload 1*  
  :param elementIndex: (long) - Element (long) index in the table's address space
  :return: (long) The long value at the specified element (long) index
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param context: (io.deephaven.db.v2.sources.chunk.ChunkSource.FillContext) - A RegionContextHolder to enable resource caching where suitable, with current
                       region index pointing to this region
  :param elementIndex: (long) - Element (long) index in the table's address space
  :return: (long) The long value at the specified element (long) index
methods.mask:
This mask is applied to OrderedKeys which are passed into
 ChunkSource.getChunk(ChunkSource.GetContext, OrderedKeys) and
 ChunkSource.fillChunk(ChunkSource.FillContext, WritableChunk, OrderedKeys). This allows the
 PagingChunkSources to be cached, and reused even if they are properly relocated in key
 space.

:return: (long) the mask for this page, which must be a bitmask representing the some number of lower order bits of a
 long.
